This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring June 15, 2014 as World Elder Abuse Awareness Day. The proclamation highlights the importance of addressing elder abuse, neglect, and exploitation, as it damages public health and affects millions of individuals. The Obama Administration is committed to ending elder abuse, supporting victims, and holding abusers accountable. The proclamation mentions the Elder Justice Act, which was enacted under the Affordable Care Act to invest in identifying, responding to, and preventing elder abuse. The government aims to bring together various stakeholders to build a more responsive criminal justice system, help seniors avoid financial scams, and prevent elder abuse before it occurs. The proclamation calls upon all Americans to observe the day by learning the signs of elder abuse and raising awareness about this issue.